'''''Dollars With Sense''''' is a television show made in [[Melbourne|Melbourne, Australia]] since 2009 that aims to educate its viewers on their finances and how to grow their wealth so that they can achieve financial freedom.

Hosted by Dallas Brooks, the show includes regular panellists Professor Allan Manning from LMI Group, Dr. Mark Sinclair from Mentor Education, Professor Sinclair Davidson from [[RMIT University]], Dr. Steven Enticott from CIA Tax, Deborah Roglien from The Intelligent Financial Group, Anouk Pinchetti from the Blockchain Centre, Colin Peirce from Lewis and Weir Lawyers and James Lynch from CastleCoin.

Brooks has the maxim that you should "work harder not smarter" and the expert panellists on the show focus on helping you grow your wealth through investing, growing your superannuation, minimizing your tax, and through business as well as various others relevant topics in way that will help you grow your wealth and secure your future.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dollarswithsense.com.au/ |title=Dollars With Sense – Work Smarter Not Harder |website=Dollarswithsense.com.au |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2016-01-08}}</ref>

