'''Erwin Conradi''' (* February 12, 1935, [[Frankfurt am Main]]) was as head of [[Metro AG]] one of the most important managers in trade business.

He studied industrial engineering, then worked from 1959 at [[IBM]] and from 1971 at Metro.

From 1996 until 2000 he was chairman of the board,<ref name="SethRandall2001">{{cite book|last1=Seth|first1=Andrew|last2=Randall|first2=Geoffrey|title=The grocers: the rise and rise of the supermarket chains|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EUq34wdocccC&pg=PA174|accessdate=9 April 2011|date=November 2001|publisher=Kogan Page Publishers|isbn=978-0-7494-3549-3|page=174}}</ref> after Kaufhaus, Asco and Cash & Carry had merged into Metro AG. 2004 he left   Metro AG.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.spiegelgruppe.de/spiegelgruppe/home.nsf/PMWeb/42BAEA72054B08B6C1256F9500415545 |title=Beisheim entlässt Conradi" |accessdate=2013-07-26 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302155208/http://www.spiegelgruppe.de/spiegelgruppe/home.nsf/PMWeb/42BAEA72054B08B6C1256F9500415545 |archivedate=March 2, 2012 |df= }} - [[manager magazin]]   14. September 2004</ref> In 1999 he received an [[honorary doctor]] from [[TU Braunschweig]].

