Count '''Richard Goblet d'Alviella''' (born 6 July 1948) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman, who studied [[economics]] at the [[Université libre de Bruxelles]], ([[Brussels]]), and obtained an [[MBA]] at the [[Harvard Business School]]. He is a son of [[Jean Goblet d'Alviella]]. On 22 July 1971, he married countess [[House of d'Oultremont|Veronique d'Oultremont]].
He is a member of the board of directors of the [[Groupe Danone]] and [[Sofina]], director and member of the audit committee of the [[Delhaize Group]], and [[SES S.A.|SES]].
